There were no Conservative women MPs east of M11
Today there are NINE

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Lucy Frazer MP is pressing the case for fairer funding for Cambs schools with the Department for Education.<a href="https://t.co/tzV3D7Lvei" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/Meadow_Balsham/status/656915120141021184" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/Meadow_Balsham/status/656915120141021184"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/Meadow_Balsham</span><span class="invisible">/status/656915120141021184</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>
</div>


<p class="u-hiddenVisually" aria-hidden="true" data-aria-label-part="3">Linton Village College added,</p>

    <script nonce="" id="track-ttft-body-script">
  if(window.ttft){
    window.ttft.recordMilestone('page', document.getElementById('swift-page-name').getAttribute('content'));
    window.ttft.recordMilestone('section', document.getElementById('swift-section-name').getAttribute('content'));
    window.ttft.recordMilestone('client_record_time', window.ttft.now());
  }
</script>
